<br>
We take 3 groups of 58+ and have them wait at the bridge before his lair. <br>
<br>
We send a Pally, or Cleric(usually our guildleader who loves this suicidal crap) to DA and move Trak to the back of his lair out of Line of Sight. After a few seconds we CoTH the DA pally/cleric back to the raid.<br>
<br>
Then I proceed to pull the Protector and whatever Juggs come(usually 4 or 5).   We leave Tola and a couple Juggs around him up....they don't aggro.<br>
<br>
We put 2 Pallies and 2 Warriors in the main group with a cleric and a CoTH mage. We put our other 2 groups in the niche just past bridge about halfway up the walkway to Trak's lair.<br>
<br>
We send up the 2 Pallies DA'd first of all. They get some Trak aggro and then call the assist. We all run up and melee's use all damage /discs as soon as fight begins. <br>
<br>
We have discovered that CoTH is a great tool to use to defeat Trak. If he banishes a tank to Shrooms, just CoTH them back. <br>
<br>
Trak goes down FAST and tries to run from the lair and WILL gate back and be about 25% health...if this happens it's doubtful you'll recover. Make sure your nukers are in melee range of Trak or the nukes will not land.<br>
